- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely, as the paper discusses programming and reasoning with coinductive types. 
- cs.LOgic (Logic in Computer Science) is another possible category, as the paper deals with the treatment of equality in type theory. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is less likely, but still possible, as the paper discusses the computational interpretation of functional extensionality and canonicity for the natural numbers type. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely, but possible, as the paper discusses the implementation of GDTT with decidable type checking.
